{
  "texts": [
    "This study utilized Pléiades stereo triplets to generate high-resolution digital elevation models (DEMs) and snow depth maps using the Ames Stereo Pipeline.",
    "Notably, 465 the evaluation was significantly bolstered by comparing the derived snow depth maps with ASO data, enhancing the accuracy and completeness assessment over 138 km² of mountainous terrain.",
    "Furthermore, the study delved into the impact of various factors such as the base-to-height ratio of stereo images, stereo algorithm, and cost function on the precision and comprehensiveness of snow depth mapping techniques (43).",
    "This approach marks a substantial step forward in refining snow depth mapping methodologies, particularly in challenging mountainous environments, 470 offering promising avenues for future research and application in snowpack monitoring and management.In a study, researchers (42) utilized Landsat-8 images to analyze changes in snow cover and vegetation.",
    "The analysis involved calculating the Normalized Difference Snow Index (NDSI) and Normalized Difference Vegetation Index (NDVI) to determine the normalized index of the difference and changes in snow cover and vegetation for 475 Landsat sensor images."
  ]
}